  "teach": {
    "type": "flashcard",
    "items": [
      {
        "front": "どこへも/なにも/だれも + negative",
        "back": "Negative universal expressions:\nどこへも行きません = don't go anywhere\nなにも食べません = don't eat anything\nだれにも会いません = don't meet anyone\n\nWith motion verbs: へも\nWith other verbs: も\n\nどこへも行きませんでした。\n= I didn't go anywhere."
      },
      {
        "front": "〜ばよかったです — I wish I had done",
        "back": "Expressing regret about the past:\n[verb ば-form] + よかったです\n\n行く → 行けばよかったです\n= I wish I had gone.\n\n食べる → 食べればよかったです\n= I wish I had eaten.\n\nUsed to express hindsight regret."
      },
      {
        "front": "〜なければよかったです — I wish I hadn't",
        "back": "Regret about something you DID do:\n[verb neg. ば-form] + よかったです\n\n食べなければよかったです。\n= I wish I hadn't eaten. (regretting eating)\n\nいいすぎなければよかったです。\n= I wish I hadn't said too much."
      }
    ]
  },
